3311.Name: MAPTA Men's PTI/Chaos in a Cage
3311.Details:
Welcome to the 2021 Men's Chaos In A Cage Tourney!  This is a minimum combined team PTI of 30. This tournament will take place on Saturday November 6th. Always been a great tourney to play with someone you don't play tournaments with and to most importantly have some fun!
32 team draw played in one day!  Men will start at 8am at Martin's Dam and Overbrook.  
Format:
Men's main draw matches will play 2 out of 3 sets using regular scoring.  Tiebreaker at 6-6.  Consolation matches will play 2 out of 3 sets using regular scoring with a super tiebreaker played in lieu of a full 3rd set.
Prizes: Winners and finalists of main draw win prizes. Only Champions of consolation brackets will win prizes.

TO REGISTER: PLEASE CLICK ON THE "REGISTER" TAB ABOVE
3311.RegistrationDetails:
Registration: Check in and pick up your favor at Overbrook between 7am-9am.
Amenities: Continental breakfast, lunch, early dinner , favor, and tons of paddle!  Cost is $180/team  
Start times will be emailed on Friday November 5th by 3pm

3323.Name: The Amateur "Open PTI"
3323.Details:
We are looking for 16 strong teams in the Fourth Annual "The Amateur" tournament being held on November 20th.  This is a PTI tournament, and I expect competitive matches throughout the day. Same as in prior years, no pros of any racket sport are eligible (including squash, ping pong, pickle and tennis). If you have a question regarding your eligibility, you probably are not eligible.

The entry fee will be $130 per team which include a minimum of 3 matches (no add and third set 10 point tie breaker), lunch, beer at Waynesborough, and a cool T-Shirt (that is an immediate collector’s edition). All matches will be played at Waynesborough or Chester Valley Golf Club.

Paul Ridder and TastyKake donate the side nourishment and Waynesborough will be doing lunch and beer.

This year we will only be registering on the www.mapta.tenniscores.com website and you will need to put your T-Shirt size for you and your partner.

Nathan Gambino and I will be running the event and my cell number is 610-547-9600 and my email is studnick@gmail.com

All the information will be on the www.mapta.tenniscores.com website under the tournament tab and registration will begin on October 18th and close on November 12th.  I do expect a wait list and we will be letting teams in based on PTI rankings and I am inviting teams from outside MAPTA to make this a really fun and competitive event.

Plan on your first match starting at 9AM at either Waynesborough or Chester. We will all have lunch at Waynesborough and then the third matches will be either at Waynesborough or Chester Valley
All four finals will be played at Waynesborough, and we can hang till we kick the keg (plan on taking an Uber home).

3338.Name: MAPTA Men's Philly Cricket Invitational PTI 5-19
3338.Details:
Welcome to the 2021 Men's Philly Cricket Invitational. This tournament is open to all players who have an individual PTI between 5 and 19. The tournament will be a 24 team draw and the lowest combined PTI teams get into the draw based on the criteria above. This tournament will take place on Saturday, December 4th. The Philadelphia Cricket Club is the main host site with Huntingdon Valley Country Club as our second site. Just a friendly reminder, just because you have registered for the event does not mean you are automatically in the draw. Entry into the tournament will be based on your PTI as of 11/29. 

Format:
Men's main draw matches will play 2 out of 3 sets using regular scoring.  Tiebreaker at 6-6.  Consolation matches will play 2 out of 3 sets using regular scoring with a super tiebreaker played in lieu of a full 3rd set. You are guaranteed 3 matches! 

Prizes: Winners and Finalists of Main Draw win prizes. 

Registration: Check in and pick up your favor at Philadelphia Cricket Club between 7am-9am.

Amenities: Beer more beer & lunch between 12:00pm & 2:00pm, favors, and tons of paddle!  Cost is $150/team  

1st round matches will start at 8:00am and start times/site will be emailed by Thursday, December 2nd.

TO REGISTER: PLEASE CLICK ON THE "REGISTER" TAB ABOVE
